	 	 	 	 HEADLINE 
Post Sridevi's demise, the Kapoors resume work
	 	 	 	 CONTENT 
Sridevi’s untimely demise a fortnight ago had left the whole country in a state of shock. The whole repatriation process took a toll on the entire Kapoor family. Still coping with their loss, the Kapoors have now started resuming work.

Anil Kapoor and Sonam Kapoor who were shooting in Chandigarh for Ek Ladki Ko Dekha Toh Aisa Laga, had taken a break from the shoot when the tragedy happened. Recently, Anil accompanied brother Boney Kapoor to Haridwar to offer prayers for Sridevi. Now, we hear the baap-beti will head back to Punjab to resume shoot for the Shelly Chopra directorial.

Arjun Kapoor who had also rushed to be with his family, has already returned to Punjab to shoot the first schedule of Namaste England. Says a source close to the family, “They are trying to bring the situation back to normal. It’s difficult, but everyone in the family is professional and they are constantly in touch, even when they are away.” Like they say, the show must go on...
